#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:22
msgid ""
"Bit arrays in general do not have a numpy equivalent and are not supported.  "
"Char arrays are also not easy to handle and might not work as you expect.  "
"Patches welcome."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:26
msgid ""
"You need to make sure you hold a reference to a Numpy array you want to "
"import into VTK.  If not you'll get a segfault (in the best case). The same "
"holds in reverse when you convert a VTK array to a numpy array -- don't "
"delete the VTK array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:32
msgid "Created by Prabhu Ramachandran in Feb. 2008."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:7
msgid ""
"This module adds support to easily import and export NumPy (http://numpy."
"scipy.org) arrays into/out of VTK arrays.  The code is loosely based on TVTK "
"(https://svn.enthought.com/enthought/wiki/TVTK)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:11
msgid ""
"This code depends on an addition to the VTK data arrays made by Berk Geveci "
"to make it support Python's buffer protocol (on Feb. 15, 2008)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:14
msgid ""
"The main functionality of this module is provided by the two functions:     "
"numpy_to_vtk,     vtk_to_numpy."
msgstr ""

